b'' b'in pc magazine april "although scsi is twice as fasst as esdi,' b'20% faster than ide, and support up to devices its acceptance ...has' b'long been stalled by incompatability problems and installation headaches."' b'' b'i love it when magazine writers make stupid statements like that re:' b"performance. where do they get those numbers? i'll list the actual" b'performance ranges, which should convince anyone that such a' b'statement is absurd:' b'scsi-i ranges from 0-5mb/s.' b'scsi-ii ranges from 0-40mb/s.' b'ide ranges from 0-8.3mb/s.' b'esdi is always 1.25mb/s (although there are some non-standard versions)' b"all this shows is that you don't know much about scsi." b'' b'scsi-1 {with a scsi-1 controler chip} range is indeed 0-5mb/s' b'and that is all you have right about scsi' b'scsi-1 {with a scsi-2 controller chip}: 4-6mb/s with 10mb/s burst {8-bit}' b'note the increase in speed, the mac quadra uses this version of scsi-1' b'so it does exist. some pc use this set up too.' b'scsi-2 {8-bit/scsi-1 mode}: 4-6mb/s with 10mb/s burst' b'scsi-2 {16-bit/wide or fast mode}: 8-12mb/s with 20mb/s burst' b'scsi-2 {32-bit/wide and fast}: 15-20mb/s with 40mb/s burst' b'' b'by your own data the "although scsi is twice as fast as esdi" is correct' b'with a scsi-2 controller chip scsi-1 can reach 10mb/s which is indeed' b'"20% faster than ide" of is all these scsi facts have been' b'posted to this newsgroup in my mac ibm info sheet {available by ftp on' b'sumex-aim.stanford.edu in the info-mac/report as' b'mac-ibm-compare[version #].txt (it should be but may still be there)}' b'' b'part of this problem is both mac and ibm pc are inconsiant about what scsi' b'is which. though it is well documented that the quadra has a scsi-2 chip' b'an apple salesperson said "it uses a fast scsi-1 chip" {not at a 6mb/s,' b'10mb/s burst it does not. scsi-1 is 5mb/s maximum synchronous and quadra' b'uses ansynchronous scsi which is slower} it seems that mac and ibm see' b"scsi-1 interface and think 'scsi-1' when it maybe a scsi-1 interface driven" b'in the machine by a scsi-2 controller chip in 8-bit mode {which is much' b'faster then true scsi-1 can go}.' b'' b"don't slam an article because you don't understand what is going on." b"one reference for the quadra's scsi-2 controller chip is" b'(digital review, oct v8 n33 p8(1)).' 